      <h1>Apache HTTP Info</h1>
      <hr>
      <div class="topic-content">
        <h2>What is apache?</h2>
        <p>Apache is an open source server application, it receives HTTP directory requests from users and sends them the information at that address. It can send files or handle reverse <a href="#PROXY_DEF">proxy requests.</a></p>
      </div>
      <div class="topic-content">
        <h2>Background</h2>
        <p>Apache is non-copyleft open source and owned by the Apache Software Foundation. They are a nonprofit organisation and based in America. The group was established on March 25, 1999 today continuing to support a number of open source software projects.</p>
      </div>
	  <div class="topic-content">
		<h2>The popularity of Apache</h2>
		<p>Apache is used by a large majority amongst the internet, even when many open source options are available such as <strong>NGINX</strong> and <strong>Node.JS</strong></p>
